      "notes": "online\n________________________________\nFrom: Ferenc Somogyi <feso24ac@student.cbs.dk>\nSent: Monday, 25 May 2026 20:55:03\nTo: Torkil Clemmensen <tc.digi@cbs.dk>\nCc: Lukas Alistair Hauge Gray <luha20ad@student.cbs.dk>\nSubject: Re: Thesis Meeting\n\nHello Torkil,\n\nWould you have time slots on 1, 3 June and between 15-17 June?\n\nDeadlines are (2nd attempt):\n\n  *   Submit contract: 1 August before 23.59 CET\n  *   Contract approval: No later than 6 weeks after 1 August\n  *   Submit thesis: 15 September before 15.59 CET\n  *   Submission on Digital Exam: 1 - 15 September (15.59 CET the 15th at the latest)\n  *   Oral defence: 16 September - 31 October\n\nFerenc and Lukas\n\nOn 18 May 2026, at 22.43, Torkil Clemmensen <tc.digi@cbs.dk> wrote:\n\nHello,\nI have a timeslot june 11 at 1300. When is you new deadline?\nCheers\nTorkil\n________________________________\nFrom: Lukas Alistair Hauge Gray <luha20ad@student.cbs.dk>\nSent: Monday, 18 May 2026 07:43:10\nTo: Torkil Clemmensen <tc.digi@cbs.dk>\nCc: Ferenc Somogyi <feso24ac@student.cbs.dk>\nSubject: Thesis Meeting\n\nHello,\nThis is Lukas Hauge Gray and Ferenc Somogyi, the two students from Digital Business who are writing our thesis on digital entrepreneurship. We are writing to let you know that we decided to delay our thesis to the second attempt due to a few factors. We are wondering if you are available for a meeting soon to discuss our project and if anything needs to change in our project, etc. Would you be available on Wednesday or Friday this week? If so, what times? And if not, how about next week?\nThank you for your time.\nKind regards,\nLukas Hauge Gray and Ferenc Somogyi\n\n________________________________________________________________________________\nMicrosoft Teams meeting\nJoin: https://teams.microsoft.com/meet/366754400738908?p=HPORCYN0cj6d4rQY03<https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/ap/t-59584e83/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fteams.microsoft.com%2Fmeet%2F366754400738908%3Fp%3